<resources>
<!--
    Here I make the app have no action bar in order for the app to have a more sleek look.

    In order to change that, you can simply remove "NoActionBar" and the application will give you
    options to help with your preference for the action bar.

    Link used for the tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ES_Zp4aAK3M

    In addition, I make my own style which helps with my pop up window, allow the user to leave the
    pop window by clicking the outside of it, whilst giving the rest of the app a darker look whilst
    reading the pop up.

    Link used for the tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eX-TdY6bLdg
-->
    <!-- Base application theme. -->
    <style name="AppTheme" parent="Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">
        <!-- Customize your theme here. -->
        <item name="colorPrimary">@color/colorPrimary</item>
        <item name="colorPrimaryDark">@color/colorPrimaryDark</item>
        <item name="colorAccent">@color/colorAccent</item>
    </style>

    <style name="AppTheme.popUp">

        <item name="android:windowIsTranslucent">true</item>
        <item name="android:windowCloseOnTouchOutside">true</item>
        <item name = "android:windowBackground" > @android:color/transparent</item>

    </style>

</resources>
